USAID representative Karen Freeman, Isiolo Governor Godana Doyo and Livestock PS Richard Lesiyampe sample products on offer during the opening of the modern livestock market in Isiolo town. Isiolo Governor Godana Doyo has urged voters to re-elect him to complete his development projects. He said his administration has transformed the county and improved the residents&#39; standards of living. The governor spoke during a tour of the new modern livestock market in Isiolo town. The market can serve over 7,000 livestock daily. &quot;We are transforming our county and our focus is to make livestock rearing profitable for our farmers. We are therefore urging voters to give us another term and we will bring more investors to grow our economy,&quot; he said. Also present was Agriculture PS Richard Lesiyampe.